    <config>
        <documentation>

V.4 Black and Decker Door Lock.

*** This driver requires at least 1.05.xx Firmware version in the lock for full functionality ***

---------- Note: To force a firmware update on the lock:  ----------
Ensure you're running a current version of ComposerPro / Director on the system.  Without the current version, the latest firmware will not be available.

1) Remove the batteries (press a key or two to eliminate any charge in the lock)
2) Put the batteries back in
3) Press the top left button 4 times
4) Press the top right button 4 times

The firmware should start updating.  If it does not, ensure that your batteries are fresh.  If you are unable to manually start the firmware update, the lock should automatically check-in for an update after the first check-in of the lock, at 3AM.
------------------------------------------------------------


This driver allows the control of a Black and Decker Zigbee-enabled Door Lock.

To control the lock on Navigator devices, you must pull in a Door Lock Relay device, and make a connection on the 'Connections' page in ComposerPro.

You must Identify the lock on the 'Connections' -&gt; Network Tab, by pressing the 'join network' button 4 times.

NOTE: Since the lock is a 'sleepy' device, to save battery, Lock, Unlock, and other commands may not happen immediately, although status change events should happen immediately on status change of the lock.  It may take up to 15-20 seconds for the lock to unlock or lock when that change is requested by the automation system.

You can configure the amount of time the lock will sleep between polls to receive commands, with the 'Lock Sleep Timer'.  Larger sleep values will increase battery life, but will cause a longer delay in having a command execute on the lock.

To setup User and Codes for the lock, use the Properties Page of the driver, and enter Name, Code for each desired code, and press the 'Set' button.  Codes will be visible on the Properties page for a while, and then will be hidden and not stored by the driver for security reasons.  The codes are still stored on the lock, and you can retrieve the list of codes from the lock, with the 'Show User Codes' action, from the 'Actions' tab.

To delete all codes for the lock, press the 'Delete All Codes' action, on the 'Actions' tab.

The following events are fired by the lock:

* Unlocked Manually -- Lock was unlocked using knob or key
* Locked Manually -- Lock was locked using knob or key
* Unlocked -- Lock was unlocked, either by a User code, or by a Navigator
* Locked -- Lock was unlocked, either by a User code, by the 'Lock' button, or by a Navigator
* Not Locked -- Lock attempted to lock, and was unable to lock (possibly jammed)
* Incorrect Code Lockout -- The incorrect code was entered 3 times, keypad has locked out for 1 minute
* Low Battery -- The batteries are getting low
* Very Low Battery -- The batteries should be replaced soon
* Battery Cannot Operate Motor -- The batteries are so low, they cannot lock / unlock the door

The following Variables are also available for programming:

* LOCKED -- Boolean variable, that indicates whether the lock is locked or not.
* USERCODE -- User Code (number) of the user that unlocked or locked the lock.
* USERNAME -- Name of the user that unlocked or locked the lock (if a name is available).
* LAST_ACTION_DESC -- Description of the last action performed on the lock.
* LOCK_LOG -- String variable that contains HTML that represents the last actions performed on the lock.  May be used in QT Navigator popups, to display the lock log.

The LAST_ACTION_DESC variable may be used in a popup or announcement, to show who locked / unlocked the door when it happens.

Changes since Version 2 of the lock driver:

* Date and time added to the 'Last Status' property
* More Efficient Queue Management of commands.  The driver no longer queues up duplicate commands
* Default User name for codes that don't have user names coming back from lock
* Displays Firmware version as a read-only property as other ZigBee drivers do
* Codes being deleted on lock are now confirmed by the lock
* Battery Level Notification
* Incorrect Code Lockout Notification

</documentation>
        <identify_text>Press the Left button 4 times to identify the Black and Decker Lock.</identify_text>
        <properties>
            <property>
                <name>Debug Mode</name>
                <type>LIST</type>
                <items>
                    <item>Off</item>
                    <item>Print</item>
                    <item>Log</item>
                    <item>Print and Log</item>
                </items>
                <default>Off</default>
                <readonly>false</readonly>
            </property>
            <property>
                <name>Lock Sleep Timer</name>
                <type>RANGED_INTEGER</type>
                <minimum>3</minimum>
                <maximum>7</maximum>
                <default>7</default>
                <readonly>false</readonly>
            </property>
            <property>
                <name># of Log Items</name>
                <type>RANGED_INTEGER</type>
                <minimum>5</minimum>
                <maximum>100</maximum>
                <default>30</default>
                <readonly>false</readonly>
            </property>
